        <exercise number="3">
            <statement><p>
                April sells environmentally friendly cleaning products. Her income consists of $200 per week plus a commission of 9% of her sales. Write an algebraic expression for April's weekly income, <m>I</m>, in terms of her sales, <m>S</m>.
                <md>
                    <mrow>\text{Income}\quad\amp=\qquad\text{Flat Rate}\quad  \amp \amp+{} \qquad \text{Commission} </mrow>
                    <mrow>\underline{\qquad\quad}\quad\amp=\qquad \underline{\qquad\qquad} \amp\amp+{} \qquad \underline{\qquad\qquad\quad} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p></statement>
            <answer><p><m>I=200+0.09 S</m></p></answer>
        </exercise>

        <exercise number="4">
            <statement><p>
                Trinh is bicycling down a mountain road that loses 500 feet in elevation for each 1 mile of road. She started at an elevation of 6300 feet. Write an expression for Trinh's elevation, <m>h</m>, in terms of the distance she has cycled, <m>d</m>.
                <md>
                    <mrow>\text{Elevation}\quad\amp=\qquad\text{Initial Elevation}\quad  \amp \amp -{} \qquad \text{Decrease} </mrow>
                    <mrow>\underline{\qquad\quad}\quad\amp=\qquad \underline{\qquad\qquad\qquad} \amp\amp -{} \qquad \underline{\qquad\qquad} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p></statement>
        </exercise>

